Perfect serving with brunch or as a healthy dinner side dish.", "datePublished": "2019-09-02T04:00:50+00:00", "image": ["https://www.ambitiouskitchen.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Roasted-Garlic-Fingerling-Potatoes-3-725x725-1.jpg", "https://www.ambitiouskitchen.com/wp-content/uploads/fly-images/35193/Roasted-Garlic-Fingerling-Potatoes-3-725x725-1-500x500-c.jpg", "https://www.ambitiouskitchen.com/wp-content/uploads/fly-images/35193/Roasted-Garlic-Fingerling-Potatoes-3-725x725-1-500x375-c.jpg", "https://www.ambitiouskitchen.com/wp-content/uploads/fly-images/35193/Roasted-Garlic-Fingerling-Potatoes-3-725x725-1-480x270-c.jpg"], "recipeYield": ["4", "4 servings"], "prepTime": "PT5M", "cookTime": "PT20M", "totalTime": "PT25M", "recipeIngredient": ["1 pound fingerling potatoes (gold or rainbow fingerlings are lovely!)", "1-2 tablespoons olive oil", "3/4 teaspoon garlic powder", "Freshly ground salt and pepper, to taste"], "recipeInstructions": [{"@type": "HowToStep", "text": "For the grilling method: Preheat grill to 400 degrees Wash your potatoes, then pat them dry. Place potatoes in a large bowl, then drizzle them with olive oil, garlic powder and salt and pepper. Place potatoes onto a large piece of foil, then add another large piece of foil on top. Seal the edges by folding a piece of foil together. Use a fork or knife to poke a hole at the top of the foil to allow some steam to escape. Place over direct heat on the preheated grill and grill for approximately 20-25 minutes or until potatoes are fork tender. This will vary depending on how large your fingerling potatoes are. Serve immediately.", "name": "For the grilling method: Preheat grill to 400 degrees Wash your potatoes, then pat them dry. Seal the edges by folding a piece of foil together. Use a fork or knife to poke a hole at the top of the foil to allow some steam to escape. Place over direct heat on the preheated grill and grill for approximately 20-25 minutes or until potatoes are fork tender. This will vary depending on how large your fingerling potatoes are. Serve immediately.", "url": "https://www.ambitiouskitchen.com/garlic-fingerling-potatoes/#wprm-recipe-35188-step-0-0"}, {"@type": "HowToStep", "text": "To roast potatoes in the oven: Preheat oven to 425 degrees Generously grease a large baking sheet with olive oil.Wash your potatoes, then pat them dry. Roast potatoes in the oven for 20-25 minutes, stirring potatoes halfway through. Another minute or two, and you will notice the butter turning a slight brown (caramel) color on the bottom of the saucepan; continue to whisk and remove from heat as soon as the butter begins to give off a nutty aroma.
